    Note over Alice,Network: ═══════════ KEY PROPERTIES ═══════════

    Note over Alice,Network: 1. INDEPENDENT COMPUTATION:<br/>   - Each provider computes allocations independently<br/>   - Same deterministic algorithm<br/>   - No coordination required<br/><br/>2. UPDATE LAW<br/>   - Remaining_Need = max(0, Declared_Need - Total_Received)<br/>   - Applied by RECIPIENTS after receiving<br/>   - Can receive from MULTIPLE providers per iteration<br/><br/>3. OVER-ALLOCATION IS EXPECTED:<br/>   - "Allocations are capped at declared need *per provider*"<br/>   - "You might receive from multiple providers in one round"<br/>   - Total can exceed need → triggers update law<br/><br/>4. CONVERGENCE:<br/>   - Total-Needs(tomorrow) ≤ Total-Needs(today)<br/>   - System contracts toward zero remaining needs<br/>   - Guaranteed if capacity sufficient<br/><br/>5. NO ACCUMULATION:<br/>   - Need(tomorrow) = Need(today) - Allocation(today)<br/>   - Receiving decreases need, never increases wealth<br/>   - "Mathematical abolition of wealth accumulation"